Both files are in place. Headline result: a five-variable subgroup (feature_001=1, feature_021=1, feature_014=1, feature_026=0, feature_009=0; n=1790, 3.6% of cohort) has ORR 78.6% vs 16.5% in everyone else (Fisher OR=18.55, p<1e-300). The three positives are statistically independent and combine via a clean 3-way interaction (no main effects survive once triple_pos is included), and the two suppressors have negligible main effects but huge interactions with triple_pos. Two further global negative prognostic factors (feature_004 ECOG-like, feature_020) act additively in both strata. transcript.json validates against the schema (13 iterations, all hypotheses paired with analyses bearing signed effect estimates and p-values).
